research_municipality_step.notes: Jersey City operates under a mayor-council government, specifically Plan C under the Optional Municipal Charter Law (Faulkner Act). The City Council consists of nine members: one for each of the six wards, and three at-large members. James Solomon assumed office as Mayor on January 15, 2026. Joyce Watterman is the current Council President. While the Council President is chosen from among the nine council members, the official City of Jersey City website's main council page lists three at-large members (Mamta Singh, Michael O. Griffin, Rolando R. Lavarro Jr.) and does not explicitly identify Joyce Watterman among them. However, other sources, including Ballotpedia, list Joyce Watterman as an At-Large Council Member. To ensure all identified elected officials are included, Joyce Watterman is listed with both 'Council President' and 'Council Member (At-Large)' roles. The ward council members and other at-large members are based on the official City of Jersey City website.
